Katara:
MY GRANDMOTHER USED TO

6
00:00:19,083 --> 00:00:21,583
TELL ME STORIES ABOUT
THE OLD DAYS--

7
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:23,000
A TIME OF PEACE,

8
00:00:23,041 --> 00:00:26,000
WHEN THE AVATAR KEPT BALANCE
BETWEEN WATER TRIBES,

9
00:00:26,041 --> 00:00:28,000
EARTH KINGDOM,
FIRE NATION,

10
00:00:28,041 --> 00:00:30,000
AND AIR NOMADS.

11
00:00:30,041 --> 00:00:32,959
BUT THAT ALL CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

12
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:40,208
ONLY THE AVATAR MASTERED
ALL FOUR ELEMENTS.

13
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:43,875
ONLY HE COULD STOP
THE RUTHLESS FIREBENDERS.

14
00:00:43,917 --> 00:00:45,709
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST,

15
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:46,709
HE VANISHED.

16
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:51,041
A HUNDRED YEARS
HAVE PASSED,

17
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:52,834
AND THE FIRE NATION
IS NEARING VICTORY

18
00:00:52,875 --> 00:00:54,834
IN THE WAR.

19
00:00:54,875 --> 00:00:56,000
TWO YEARS AGO,

20
00:00:56,041 --> 00:00:57,208
MY FATHER AND
THE MEN OF MY TRIBE

21
00:00:57,250 --> 00:00:58,875
JOURNEYED TO
THE EARTH KINGDOM

22
00:00:58,917 --> 00:01:00,667
TO HELP FIGHT AGAINST
THE FIRE NATION,

23
00:01:00,709 --> 00:01:03,667
LEAVING ME AND MY BROTHER
TO LOOK AFTER OUR TRIBE.

24
00:01:04,875 --> 00:01:06,333
SOME PEOPLE BELIEVE
THAT THE AVATAR

25
00:01:06,375 --> 00:01:08,375
WAS NEVER REBORN
INTO THE AIR NOMADS,

26
00:01:08,417 --> 00:01:10,333
AND THAT THE CYCLE
IS BROKEN.

27
00:01:10,375 --> 00:01:12,458
BUT I HAVEN'T
LOST HOPE.

28
00:01:13,041 --> 00:01:14,834
I STILL BELIEVE
THAT SOMEHOW

29
00:01:14,875 --> 00:01:18,291
THE AVATAR WILL RETURN
TO SAVE THE WORLD.

30
00:02:03,041 --> 00:02:05,000
IT'S NOT GETTING AWAY
FROM ME THIS TIME.

31
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:07,000
WATCH AND LEARN,
KATARA.

32
00:02:07,041 --> 00:02:08,166
THIS IS HOW
YOU CATCH A FISH.

33
00:02:18,834 --> 00:02:20,709
SOKKA, LOOK!

34
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,542
SHH, KATARA.

35
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:24,875
YOU'RE GONNA
SCARE IT AWAY.

36
00:02:24,917 --> 00:02:26,750
MMM. I CAN ALREADY
SMELL IT COOKING.

37
00:02:26,792 --> 00:02:29,500
BUT, SOKKA,
I CAUGHT ONE.

38
00:02:29,542 --> 00:02:32,625
HEY!

39
00:02:32,667 --> 00:02:34,333
AAH!

40
00:02:34,375 --> 00:02:36,208
WHY IS IT
THAT EVERY TIME

41
00:02:36,250 --> 00:02:37,917
YOU PLAY WITH
MAGIC WATER,

42
00:02:37,959 --> 00:02:39,792
I GET SOAKED?

43
00:02:39,834 --> 00:02:42,625
OHH. IT'S NOT MAGIC.
IT'S WATERBENDING.

44
00:02:42,667 --> 00:02:44,625
AND IT'S--

45
00:02:44,667 --> 00:02:46,250
YEAH, YEAH--AN ANCIENT ART
UNIQUE TO OUR CULTURE,

46
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,041
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH...

47
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:49,959
LOOK, I'M JUST SAYING
THAT IF I HAD WEIRD POWERS,

48
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,667
I'D KEEP MY WEIRDNESS
TO MYSELF.

49
00:02:51,709 --> 00:02:53,667
YOU'RE CALLING ME WEIRD?

50
00:02:53,709 --> 00:02:55,959
I'M NOT THE ONE WHO MAKES
MUSCLES AT MYSELF

51
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,542
EVERY TIME I SEE
MY REFLECTION

52
00:02:57,583 --> 00:02:58,583
IN THE WATER.

53
00:03:00,875 --> 00:03:02,000
AAH!

54
00:03:05,792 --> 00:03:07,792
[CRASH]

55
00:03:07,834 --> 00:03:10,500
[MOANING]

56
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:14,458
[MOANING]

57
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,041
WATCH OUT!

58
00:03:16,709 --> 00:03:17,709
AAH!
GO LEFT!

59
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:19,083
GO LEFT!

60
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,625
AAH!

61
00:03:24,667 --> 00:03:25,959
AAH!

62
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,583
YOU CALL THAT
LEFT?

63
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:34,458
YOU DON'T LIKE
MY STEERING.

64
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,834
WELL, MAYBE
YOU SHOULD HAVE

65
00:03:35,875 --> 00:03:37,166
WATERBENDED US
OUT OF THE ICE.

66
00:03:37,208 --> 00:03:38,625
SO IT'S MY FAULT.

67
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:40,291
I KNEW I SHOULD HAVE
LEFT YOU HOME.

68
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,709
LEAVE IT TO A GIRL
TO SCREW THINGS UP.

69
00:03:43,959 --> 00:03:47,583
YOU ARE THE MOST
SEXIST, IMMATURE,

70
00:03:47,625 --> 00:03:49,291
NUTBRAINED--

71
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:51,709
AH! I'M EMBARRASSED
TO BE RELATED TO YOU!

72
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:53,166
[CRACK]

73
00:03:53,208 --> 00:03:55,834
EVER SINCE MOM DIED,

74
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,625
I'VE BEEN DOING ALL
THE WORK AROUND CAMP,

75
00:03:57,667 --> 00:03:59,166
WHILE YOU'VE BEEN OFF
PLAYING SOLDIER.

76
00:03:59,208 --> 00:04:01,083
AH...KATARA...

77
00:04:01,125 --> 00:04:03,125
I EVEN WASH
ALL THE CLOTHES.

78
00:04:03,166 --> 00:04:05,417
HAVE YOU EVER SMELLED
YOUR DIRTY SOCKS?

79
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:07,166
LET ME TELL YOU.

80
00:04:07,208 --> 00:04:08,667
NOT PLEASANT!

81
00:04:08,709 --> 00:04:10,667
KATARA! SETTLE DOWN!

82
00:04:10,709 --> 00:04:13,458
NO! THAT'S IT.
I'M DONE HELPING YOU.

83
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:16,166
FROM NOW ON,
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN!

84
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:17,834
[CRACK]

85
00:04:17,875 --> 00:04:19,041
OH!
AAH!

86
00:04:19,083 --> 00:04:20,583
[LOUD SPLASH]

87
00:04:20,625 --> 00:04:22,875
AAH!

88
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,792
OK. YOU'VE GONE

89
00:04:30,834 --> 00:04:32,625
FROM WEIRD TO
FREAKISH, KATARA.

90
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,542
YOU MEAN,
I DID THAT?

91
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:36,875
YEP.
CONGRATULATIONS.

92
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:41,625
OH!
OH!

93
00:05:07,583 --> 00:05:09,208
AH!
UH!

94
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:12,041
HE'S ALIVE.
WE HAVE TO HELP.

95
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:14,166
KATARA!
GET BACK HERE!

96
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:15,583
WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT THING IS.

97
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:22,709
UH!

98
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:23,750
UH!

99
00:05:23,792 --> 00:05:26,542
UH! UH!

100
00:05:26,583 --> 00:05:27,500
AAH!

101
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,166
[ROARING]

102
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:51,208
FINALLY.

103
00:05:51,250 --> 00:05:53,834
UNCLE, DO YOU REALIZE
WHAT THIS MEANS?

104
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:56,208
I WON'T GET TO
FINISH MY GAME?

105
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,792
IT MEANS MY SEARCH
IS ABOUT TO

106
00:05:57,834 --> 00:05:59,250
COME TO AN END.

107
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:02,000
AHH...

108
00:06:02,041 --> 00:06:03,000
THAT LIGHT CAME FROM

109
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:05,041
AN INCREDIBLY
POWERFUL SOURCE.

110
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:06,208
IT HAS TO BE HIM.

111
00:06:06,250 --> 00:06:09,208
OR IT'S JUST
THE CELESTIAL LIGHTS.

112
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:11,542
WE'VE BEEN DOWN
THIS ROAD BEFORE,

113
00:06:11,583 --> 00:06:12,417
PRINCE ZUKO.

114
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:14,000
I DON'T WANT YOU

115
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:17,000
TO GET TOO EXCITED
OVER NOTHING.

116
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:18,792
PLEASE, SIT.

117
00:06:18,834 --> 00:06:20,417
WHY DON'T YOU ENJOY

118
00:06:20,458 --> 00:06:23,458
A CUP OF CALMING
JASMINE TEA?

119
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,417
I DON'T NEED
ANY CALMING TEA!

120
00:06:25,458 --> 00:06:27,500
I NEED TO CAPTURE
THE AVATAR!

121
00:06:27,542 --> 00:06:29,625
HELMSMEN, HEAD A COURSE
FOR THE LIGHT.

122
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,542
[WIND BLOWING]

123
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,667
STOP!

124
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:01,208
AH!

125
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,542
UH!

126
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:07,667
STOP IT!

127
00:07:12,709 --> 00:07:15,166
MMM...

128
00:07:15,208 --> 00:07:16,291
AH!

129
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:22,500
I NEED TO
ASK YOU SOMETHING.

130
00:07:22,542 --> 00:07:23,834
WHAT?

131
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,834
PLEASE,
COME CLOSER.

132
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:26,542
WHAT IS IT?

133
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,375
WILL YOU GO
PENGUIN-SLEDDING WITH ME?

134
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:32,500
AH...SURE!

135
00:07:32,542 --> 00:07:34,625
I GUESS.

136
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:36,291
UH!

137
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:37,333
WHAT'S
GOING ON HERE?

138
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:38,667
YOU TELL US!

139
00:07:38,709 --> 00:07:40,458
HOW DID YOU
GET IN THE ICE?

140
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,959
AND WHY AREN'T
YOU FROZEN?

141
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,375
I'M NOT SURE.

142
00:07:43,417 --> 00:07:44,375
[GROWLING]

143
00:07:44,417 --> 00:07:46,083
AH! UH!

144
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:47,125
UH!

145
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:48,166
[GROWLING]

146
00:07:48,208 --> 00:07:50,291
AH!

147
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:52,500
APPA, ARE YOU
ALL RIGHT?

148
00:07:52,542 --> 00:07:55,208
WAKE UP, BUDDY.

149
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:01,458
UNH! UNH!

150
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,458
AAH!

151
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,625
UNH!

152
00:08:04,667 --> 00:08:08,041
HA HA!
YOU'RE OK.

153
00:08:13,041 --> 00:08:14,583
WHAT IS
THAT THING?

154
00:08:14,625 --> 00:08:16,458
THIS IS APPA,
MY FLYING BISON.

155
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,625
RIGHT.
AND THIS IS KATARA,
MY FLYING SISTER.

156
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:23,417
GRRR.

157
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:25,834
LOOK OUT!

158
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:29,041
OH! UGH! UGH!

159
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:31,625
AGH! AGH!

160
00:08:31,667 --> 00:08:33,000
DON'T WORRY.
IT'LL WASH OUT.

161
00:08:33,041 --> 00:08:35,750
AGH!

162
00:08:35,792 --> 00:08:37,625
SO, DO YOU GUYS
LIVE AROUND HERE?

163
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:39,083
DON'T ANSWER
THAT.

164
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:40,166
DID YOU SEE
THAT CRAZY

165
00:08:40,208 --> 00:08:42,041
BOLT OF LIGHT?

166
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:43,792
HE WAS PROBABLY
TRYING TO SIGNAL
THE FIRE NAVY.

167
00:08:43,834 --> 00:08:45,500
OH, YEAH. I'M SURE
HE'S A SPY FOR THE FIRE NAVY.

168
00:08:45,542 --> 00:08:47,625
YOU CAN TELL BY
THAT EVIL LOOK IN HIS EYE.

169
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:52,625
THE PARANOID ONE
IS MY BROTHER SOKKA.

170
00:08:52,667 --> 00:08:54,208
YOU NEVER TOLD US
YOUR NAME.

171
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,542
I'M--AH! AH!

172
00:08:56,583 --> 00:08:59,500
AH! AH! AH!

173
00:08:59,542 --> 00:09:01,875
AH-CHOO!

174
00:09:01,917 --> 00:09:03,208
[WIND BLOWING]

175
00:09:08,792 --> 00:09:11,959
I'M AANG.

176
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,542
YOU JUST
SNEEZED

177
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:15,625
AND FLEW
10 FEET
IN THE AIR.

178
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:17,208
REALLY? IT FELT
HIGHER THAN THAT.

179
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:19,333
OH! YOU'RE
AN AIRBENDER.

180
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:20,458
SURE AM.

181
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,000
GIANT
LIGHT BEAMS,

182
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:23,667
FLYING BISON,
AIRBENDERS--

183
00:09:23,709 --> 00:09:25,583
I THINK I GOT
MIDNIGHT SUN
MADNESS.

184
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:27,625
I'M GOING HOME TO
WHERE STUFF MAKES SENSE.

185
00:09:31,542 --> 00:09:33,291
WELL, IF YOU GUYS
ARE STUCK,

186
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,542
APPA AND I CAN GIVE
YOU A LIFT.

187
00:09:38,542 --> 00:09:40,166
WE'D LOVE A RIDE.
THANKS.

188
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:42,000
OH, NO!
I AM NOT GETTING

189
00:09:42,041 --> 00:09:43,792
ON THAT FLUFFY
SNOT MONSTER.

190
00:09:43,834 --> 00:09:45,667
ARE YOU HOPING
SOME OTHER

191
00:09:45,709 --> 00:09:47,000
KIND OF MONSTER
WILL COME ALONG

192
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:48,500
AND GIVE YOU
A RIDE HOME?

193
00:09:48,542 --> 00:09:50,542
YOU KNOW, BEFORE
YOU FREEZE TO DEATH.

194
00:09:50,583 --> 00:09:52,375
AH--

195
00:09:52,417 --> 00:09:54,583
[SIGHS]

196
00:09:54,625 --> 00:09:58,542
OK. FIRST-TIME FLYERS,
HOLD ON TIGHT.

197
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:01,583
APPA, YIP YIP.

198
00:10:01,625 --> 00:10:03,291
Appa: GRR.

199
00:10:09,792 --> 00:10:12,208
Aang: COME ON, APPA,
YIP YIP.

200
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:15,250
WOW, THAT WAS
TRULY AMAZING.

201
00:10:15,291 --> 00:10:17,667
APPA'S JUST TIRED.
A LITTLE REST

202
00:10:17,709 --> 00:10:19,333
AND HE'LL BE SOARING
THROUGH THE SKY.
YOU'LL SEE.

203
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:25,458
WHY ARE YOU SMILING
AT ME LIKE THAT?

204
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,417
OH. I WAS SMILING?

205
00:10:27,458 --> 00:10:28,875
ARGH!

206
00:10:43,458 --> 00:10:45,250
I'M GOING
TO BED NOW.

207
00:10:45,291 --> 00:10:47,709
[YAWN]

208
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:52,291
YEP. A MAN
NEEDS HIS REST.

209
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:56,667
PRINCE ZUKO,
YOU NEED SOME SLEEP.

210
00:10:56,709 --> 00:10:58,834
EVEN IF YOU'RE RIGHT

211
00:10:58,875 --> 00:11:02,792
AND THE AVATAR IS ALIVE,
YOU WON'T FIND HIM.

212
00:11:02,834 --> 00:11:05,750
YOUR FATHER, GRANDFATHER,

213
00:11:05,792 --> 00:11:09,500
AND GREAT-GRANDFATHER
ALL TRIED AND FAILED.

214
00:11:09,542 --> 00:11:13,166
BECAUSE THEIR HONOR DIDN'T HINGE
ON THE AVATAR'S CAPTURE.

215
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,917
MINE DOES.

216
00:11:14,959 --> 00:11:17,166
THIS COWARD'S HUNDRED YEARS
IN HIDING ARE OVER.

217
00:11:28,542 --> 00:11:30,208
HEY.

218
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:32,583
HEY. WHAT ARE YOU
THINKING ABOUT?

219
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:34,125
I GUESS I WAS WONDERING.

220
00:11:34,166 --> 00:11:36,291
YOUR BEING
AN AIRBENDER AND ALL...

221
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:38,750
IF YOU HAD ANY IDEA
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE AVATAR.

222
00:11:38,792 --> 00:11:42,500
UH...NO.
I DIDN'T KNOW HIM.

223
00:11:42,542 --> 00:11:44,583
I MEAN, I KNEW PEOPLE
THAT KNEW HIM.

224
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:46,834
BUT I DIDN'T.
SORRY.

225
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:48,583
OK. JUST CURIOUS.

226
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:49,625
GOOD NIGHT.

227
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,792
SLEEP TIGHT.

228
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:02,417
[THUNDER AND LIGHTNING]

229
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:03,583
AHH!

230
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:11,500
AAH!

231
00:12:15,625 --> 00:12:17,583
[ROAR]

232
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:38,125
Katara: AANG.
AANG, WAKE UP!

233
00:12:38,166 --> 00:12:39,458
AH!

234
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,709
IT'S OK.

235
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:41,959
WE'RE IN
THE VILLAGE NOW.

236
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,000
COME ON, GET READY.

237
00:12:43,041 --> 00:12:44,166
EVERYONE'S WAITING
TO MEET YOU.

238
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:49,083
OH!

239
00:12:52,542 --> 00:12:54,125
AAH!

240
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,208
AANG, THIS IS

241
00:13:01,250 --> 00:13:03,041
THE ENTIRE VILLAGE.

242
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:04,083
ENTIRE VILLAGE,

243
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:05,709
AANG.

244
00:13:07,625 --> 00:13:09,625
UH...

245
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:12,166
WHY ARE THEY ALL
LOOKING AT ME
LIKE THAT?

246
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:14,083
DID APPA
SNEEZE ON ME?

247
00:13:14,125 --> 00:13:15,709
WELL, NO ONE
HAS SEEN
AN AIRBENDER

248
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,375
IN A HUNDRED YEARS.

249
00:13:17,417 --> 00:13:18,875
WE THOUGHT
THEY WERE EXTINCT.

250
00:13:18,917 --> 00:13:20,291
UNTIL MY GRANDDAUGHTER
AND GRANDSON

251
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,458
FOUND YOU.

252
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,166
EXTINCT?

253
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:24,834
AANG, THIS IS
MY GRANDMOTHER.

254
00:13:24,875 --> 00:13:27,500
CALL ME GRAN GRAN.

255
00:13:27,542 --> 00:13:29,250
WHAT IS THIS,
A WEAPON?

256
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:31,125
YOU CAN'T STAB
ANYTHING WITH THIS.

257
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:34,500
IT'S NOT FOR STABBING.
IT'S FOR AIRBENDING.

258
00:13:34,542 --> 00:13:35,917
AH!

259
00:13:35,959 --> 00:13:38,458
MAGIC TRICK,
DO IT AGAIN.

260
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:41,333
NOT MAGIC,
AIRBENDING.

261
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:44,125
IT LETS ME CONTROL
THE AIR CURRENTS AROUND
MY GLIDER AND FLY.

262
00:13:44,166 --> 00:13:46,083
YOU KNOW,
LAST TIME I CHECKED,

263
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:47,959
HUMANS CAN'T FLY.

264
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,709
CHECK AGAIN!

265
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:51,875
AH!

266
00:13:51,917 --> 00:13:53,750
WOW, HE'S FLYING.

267
00:13:57,417 --> 00:13:58,917
HE'S AMAZING!

268
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:05,583
UNH!

269
00:14:07,583 --> 00:14:10,875
UH! UH!

270
00:14:10,917 --> 00:14:12,959
OH! MY WATCHTOWER.

271
00:14:15,917 --> 00:14:18,125
THAT WAS AMAZING.

272
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:23,625
UH!

273
00:14:23,667 --> 00:14:25,375
GREAT.

274
00:14:25,417 --> 00:14:27,500
YOU'RE AN AIRBENDER,
KATARA'S A WATERBENDER.

275
00:14:27,542 --> 00:14:30,083
TOGETHER YOU CAN JUST
WASTE TIME ALL DAY LONG.

276
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:31,500
YOU'RE A WATERBENDER!

277
00:14:31,542 --> 00:14:34,250
WELL, SORT OF.
NOT YET.

278
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,875
ALL RIGHT.
NO MORE PLAYING.

279
00:14:35,917 --> 00:14:39,291
COME ON, KATARA.
YOU HAVE CHORES.

280
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:41,917
Katara: I TOLD YOU.
HE'S THE REAL THING, GRAN GRAN.

281
00:14:41,959 --> 00:14:44,125
I FINALLY FOUND
A BENDER TO TEACH ME.

282
00:14:44,166 --> 00:14:46,458
KATARA, TRY NOT TO
PUT ALL YOUR HOPES

283
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,834
IN THIS BOY.

284
00:14:47,875 --> 00:14:50,083
BUT HE'S SPECIAL.
I CAN TELL.

285
00:14:50,125 --> 00:14:53,333
I SENSE HE'S FILLED
WITH MUCH WISDOM.

286
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:56,792
SEE? NOW MY TONGUE IS
STUCK TO MY STAFF!

287
00:14:56,834 --> 00:14:58,542
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

288
00:15:03,917 --> 00:15:05,458
AGAIN.

289
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:09,458
AH! HIYA!

290
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:12,500
AHH. NO!

291
00:15:12,542 --> 00:15:15,208
POWER AND FIREBENDING
COME FROM THE BREATH,

292
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:17,417
NOT THE MUSCLES.

293
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:21,083
THE BREATH BECOMES
ENERGY IN THE BODY.

294
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:23,750
THE ENERGY EXTENDS
PAST YOUR LIMBS

295
00:15:23,792 --> 00:15:25,625
AND BECOMES FIRE!

296
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:27,959
GET IT RIGHT THIS TIME.

297
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,542
ENOUGH.

298
00:15:29,583 --> 00:15:31,625
I'VE BEEN DRILLING
THIS SEQUENCE ALL DAY.

299
00:15:31,667 --> 00:15:33,208
TEACH ME THE NEXT SET.

300
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,625
I'M MORE THAN READY.

301
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,125
NO! YOU'RE IMPATIENT.

302
00:15:36,166 --> 00:15:38,500
YOU HAVE YET TO
MASTER YOUR BASICS.

303
00:15:38,542 --> 00:15:40,041
DRILL IT AGAIN!

304
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:41,500
AHH! HIYA!

305
00:15:41,542 --> 00:15:43,834
UH!

306
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:48,000
THE SAGES TELL US
THAT THE AVATAR IS
THE LAST AIRBENDER.

307
00:15:48,041 --> 00:15:51,041
HE MUST BE OVER
A HUNDRED YEARS OLD
BY NOW.

308
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:54,125
HE'S HAD A CENTURY TO
MASTER THE 4 ELEMENTS.

309
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:57,125
I'LL NEED MORE THAN
BASIC FIREBENDING
TO DEFEAT HIM.

310
00:15:57,166 --> 00:15:58,959
YOU WILL TEACH ME
THE ADVANCED SET!

311
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,750
VERY WELL.
BUT FIRST,

312
00:16:02,792 --> 00:16:06,458
I MUST FINISH
MY ROAST DUCK.

313
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,792
YUM, YUM, YUM.

314
00:16:10,208 --> 00:16:12,750
NOW, MEN, IT'S IMPORTANT
THAT YOU SHOW NO FEAR

315
00:16:12,792 --> 00:16:14,709
WHEN YOU FACE A FIREBENDER.

316
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:18,333
IN THE WATER TRIBE, WE FIGHT
TILL THE LAST MAN'S STANDING.

317
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:20,625
FOR WITHOUT COURAGE,
HOW CAN WE CALL OURSELVES MEN?

318
00:16:23,542 --> 00:16:25,500
I GOTTA PEE.

319
00:16:25,542 --> 00:16:28,375
LISTEN! UNTIL YOUR FATHERS
RETURN FROM THE WAR,

320
00:16:28,417 --> 00:16:30,583
THEY'RE COUNTING ON YOU
TO BE THE MEN OF THIS TRIBE.

321
00:16:30,625 --> 00:16:33,208
AND THAT MEANS,
NO POTTY BREAKS.

322
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:34,542
BUT I REALLY GOTTA GO.

323
00:16:34,583 --> 00:16:35,959
[SIGHS]

324
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,792
OK. WHO ELSE HAS TO GO?

325
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:41,625
UH!

326
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,458
HAVE YOU SEEN AANG?

327
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:46,667
GRAN GRAN SAID
HE DISAPPEARED
OVER AN HOUR AGO.

328
00:16:46,709 --> 00:16:49,458
WOW! EVERYTHING FREEZES
IN THERE.

329
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,125
[LAUGHING]

330
00:16:51,166 --> 00:16:53,041
AH! KATARA, GET HIM
OUT OF HERE.

331
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:55,625
THIS LESSON IS
FOR WARRIORS ONLY.

332
00:16:55,667 --> 00:16:56,458
WEE!

333
00:16:56,500 --> 00:16:58,500
HA! HA! HA!

334
00:16:58,542 --> 00:16:59,542
[LAUGHING]

335
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,542
HA! HA! HA!

336
00:17:01,583 --> 00:17:04,166
STOP! STOP IT
RIGHT NOW!

337
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:05,709
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

338
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:07,583
WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR FUN AND GAMES

339
00:17:07,625 --> 00:17:08,583
WITH A WAR GOING ON!

340
00:17:08,625 --> 00:17:10,166
WHAT WAR?

341
00:17:10,208 --> 00:17:11,750
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

342
00:17:11,792 --> 00:17:12,750
YOU'RE KIDDING,
RIGHT?

343
00:17:12,792 --> 00:17:15,500
PENGUIN!

344
00:17:15,542 --> 00:17:18,083
OH!

345
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:23,500
HE'S KIDDING, RIGHT?

346
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:32,500
AANG!

347
00:17:32,542 --> 00:17:35,917
HA! HA! HEY, COME ON,
LITTLE GUY.

348
00:17:35,959 --> 00:17:37,542
WANNA GO SLEDDING?
UNH!

349
00:17:40,792 --> 00:17:42,375
I HAVE A WAY
WITH ANIMALS.

350
00:17:42,417 --> 00:17:45,583
YACK! YACK! YACK!
YACK! YACK!

351
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:47,166
HA HA HA!

352
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:49,417
AANG, I'LL HELP YOU
CATCH A PENGUIN

353
00:17:49,458 --> 00:17:52,000
IF YOU TEACH ME
WATERBENDING.

354
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,333
YOU GOT A DEAL.

355
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:54,875
JUST ONE LITTLE PROBLEM.

356
00:17:54,917 --> 00:17:58,000
I'M AN AIRBENDER,
NOT A WATERBENDER.

357
00:17:58,041 --> 00:18:00,583
ISN'T THERE SOMEONE
IN YOUR TRIBE
WHO CAN TEACH YOU?

358
00:18:00,625 --> 00:18:03,458
NO. YOU'RE LOOKING AT
THE ONLY WATERBENDER

359
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:05,291
IN THE WHOLE SOUTH POLE.

360
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:06,834
THIS ISN'T RIGHT.

361
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:08,583
A WATERBENDER
NEEDS TO MASTER WATER.

362
00:18:09,875 --> 00:18:11,542
WHAT ABOUT THE NORTH POLE?

363
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:14,000
THERE'S ANOTHER WATER TRIBE
UP THERE, RIGHT?

364
00:18:14,041 --> 00:18:16,583
MAYBE THEY HAVE
WATERBENDERS
WHO COULD TEACH YOU.

365
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:18,417
MAYBE, BUT WE
HAVEN'T HAD CONTACT

366
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:21,000
WITH OUR SISTER TRIBE
IN A LONG TIME.

367
00:18:21,041 --> 00:18:23,959
IT'S NOT EXACTLY
TURN RIGHT AT
THE SECOND GLACIER.

368
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,625
IT'S ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE WORLD.

369
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:28,417
BUT YOU FORGET.
I HAVE A FLYING BISON.

370
00:18:28,458 --> 00:18:32,000
APPA AND I CAN PERSONALLY
FLY YOU TO THE NORTH POLE.

371
00:18:32,041 --> 00:18:34,208
KATARA, WE'RE GONNA
FIND YOU A MASTER.

372
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:36,625
THAT'S--I MEAN...

373
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:39,417
I DON'T KNOW.
I'VE NEVER LEFT HOME BEFORE.

374
00:18:39,458 --> 00:18:40,959
WELL, YOU THINK
ABOUT IT.

375
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,250
BUT IN THE MEANTIME,

376
00:18:42,291 --> 00:18:44,500
CAN YOU TEACH ME
TO CATCH ONE OF
THESE PENGUINS?

377
00:18:44,542 --> 00:18:48,208
OK. LISTEN CLOSELY,
MY YOUNG PUPIL.

378
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:52,208
CATCHING PENGUINS IS
AN ANCIENT AND SACRED ART.

379
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:53,250
OBSERVE.

380
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:56,667
[SQUAWKING]

381
00:18:56,709 --> 00:18:59,792
HA! HA! HA! HA!

382
00:19:03,792 --> 00:19:06,834
AAH!

383
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:07,917
[LAUGHING]

384
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:13,166
HA! HA! YEAH!

385
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:16,083
HA! HA! HA! HA!

386
00:19:16,125 --> 00:19:17,542
WHOO!

387
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:20,625
[LAUGHING]

388
00:19:20,667 --> 00:19:23,583
I HAVEN'T DONE THIS
SINCE I WAS A KID.

389
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:24,959
YOU STILL ARE A KID.

390
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,834
[LAUGHING]

391
00:19:45,750 --> 00:19:48,333
WHOA.

392
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:50,125
WHAT IS THAT?

393
00:19:50,166 --> 00:19:52,667
A FIRE NAVY SHIP

394
00:19:52,709 --> 00:19:57,083
AND A VERY BAD MEMORY
FOR MY PEOPLE.

395
00:19:57,125 --> 00:19:59,667
AANG, STOP.

396
00:19:59,709 --> 00:20:01,625
WE'RE NOT ALLOWED
TO GO NEAR IT.

397
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:03,208
THE SHIP COULD BE
BOOBY-TRAPPED.

398
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,291
IF YOU WANT
TO BE A BENDER,

399
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:05,417
YOU HAVE TO
LET GO OF FEAR.

400
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:54,625
THIS SHIP IS HAUNTED
BY TRIBES

401
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:56,792
SINCE GRAN GRAN
WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

402
00:20:56,834 --> 00:20:58,750
IT WAS PART OF
THE FIRE NATION'S
FIRST ATTACKS.

403
00:20:58,792 --> 00:21:02,125
OK. BACK UP.

404
00:21:02,166 --> 00:21:03,667
I HAVE FRIENDS
ALL OVER THE WORLD,

405
00:21:03,709 --> 00:21:05,417
EVEN IN THE FIRE NATION.

406
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:07,291
I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANY WAR.

407
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:09,458
AANG, HOW LONG
WERE YOU IN
THAT ICEBERG?

408
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:12,625
I DON'T KNOW.
A FEW DAYS MAYBE.

409
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:15,500
I THINK IT WAS MORE
LIKE A HUNDRED YEARS.

410
00:21:15,542 --> 00:21:17,625
WHAT? THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

411
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:20,041
DO I LOOK LIKE
A 112-YEAR OLD MAN TO YOU?

412
00:21:20,083 --> 00:21:21,542
THINK ABOUT IT.

413
00:21:21,583 --> 00:21:23,208
THE WAR IS
A CENTURY OLD.

414
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:26,458
YOU DON'T KNOW ABOUT
IT, BECAUSE SOMEHOW

415
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,875
YOU WERE IN THERE
THAT WHOLE TIME.

416
00:21:28,917 --> 00:21:32,208
IT'S THE ONLY
EXPLANATION.

417
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:34,583
A HUNDRED YEARS.

418
00:21:34,625 --> 00:21:36,375
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

419
00:21:36,417 --> 00:21:38,125
I'M SORRY, AANG.

420
00:21:38,166 --> 00:21:39,792
MAYBE, SOMEHOW,

421
00:21:39,834 --> 00:21:41,583
THERE'S
A BRIGHT SIDE
TO ALL THIS.

422
00:21:41,625 --> 00:21:42,750
I DID GET TO MEET YOU.

423
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:46,500
COME ON. LET'S GET
OUT OF HERE.

424
00:21:52,834 --> 00:21:54,625
AANG,
LET'S HEAD BACK.

425
00:21:54,667 --> 00:21:56,417
THIS PLACE
IS CREEPY.

426
00:21:56,458 --> 00:21:57,458
HUH?

427
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:02,125
WHAT'S THAT YOU SAID
ABOUT BOOBY TRAPS?

428
00:22:03,542 --> 00:22:05,333
[GASPS]

429
00:22:05,375 --> 00:22:07,166
AH!

430
00:22:10,542 --> 00:22:11,625
UH-OH.

431
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:17,667
HOLD ON TIGHT!

432
00:22:19,041 --> 00:22:19,875
AAH!

433
00:22:28,959 --> 00:22:31,583
THE LAST AIRBENDER.

434
00:22:31,625 --> 00:22:34,625
QUITE AGILE
FOR HIS OLD AGE.

435
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:36,041
WAKE MY UNCLE!

436
00:22:36,083 --> 00:22:38,583
TELL HIM
I FOUND THE AVATAR.

437
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:47,083
AS WELL AS
HIS HIDING PLACE. 

438
00:23:00,458 --> 00:23:02,041
♪
